  ## Additional context and logs
  
  The Graal PR Spring PetClinic gate is failing because embedded Tomcat hits missing runtime reflection metadata.
  
  Affected jobs:
  
  - Current defaults: `Weekly Spring Tests`, job `80600494789`
  - `--future-defaults=all`: job `80600660682`
  - PetClinic checkout: `spring-projects/spring-petclinic@a2c2ef994340d3970eb6db51247456a51bb161f8`
  - PetClinic uses Spring Boot `4.0.3`
  
  The native image build succeeds. The failure happens when `./gradlew nativeTest` launches the generated native test executable.
  
  Primary failure:
  
  ```text
  org.graalvm.nativeimage.MissingReflectionRegistrationError:
  Cannot reflectively invoke method
  public java.lang.String org.apache.coyote.AbstractProtocol.getProperty(java.lang.String)
  ```
  
  Relevant path:
  
  ```text
  Spring Boot TomcatWebServer.disableBindOnInit()
    -> Connector.getProperty("bindOnInit")
    -> Tomcat IntrospectionUtils.getProperty(...)
    -> reflectively invokes AbstractProtocol.getProperty(String)
  ```
  
  This is not JaCoCo, not Docker/Testcontainers, and not future-defaults-specific. It is a missing reachability metadata problem exposed by PetClinic's Spring Boot/Tomcat startup path under strict missing-registration behavior.
  
  The direct metadata suggested by the error is:
  
  ```json
  {
    "type": "org.apache.coyote.AbstractProtocol",
    "methods": [
      {
        "name": "getProperty",
        "parameterTypes": ["java.lang.String"]
      }
    ]
  }
  ```
  
  I would also expect `setProperty(String,String)` to be needed next, because Boot sets `bindOnInit=false` after reading it:
  
  ```json
  {
    "condition": {
      "typeReached": "org.apache.tomcat.util.IntrospectionUtils"
    },
    "type": "org.apache.coyote.AbstractProtocol",
    "methods": [
      {
        "name": "getProperty",
        "parameterTypes": ["java.lang.String"]
      },
      {
        "name": "setProperty",
        "parameterTypes": ["java.lang.String", "java.lang.String"]
      }
    ]
  }
  ```
  
  The metadata repo already has:
  
  ```text
  metadata/org.apache.tomcat.embed/tomcat-embed-core/11.0.18/reachability-metadata.json
  ```
  
  but it does not register `AbstractProtocol.getProperty(String)`.
  
  Suggested test coverage: add or adjust the Tomcat metadata test to exercise:
  
  ```java
  Connector connector = new Connector();
  connector.getProperty("bindOnInit");
  connector.setProperty("bindOnInit", "false");
  ```
  
  This reproduces the same Tomcat reflection path that Spring Boot's `TomcatWebServer.disableBindOnInit()` triggers.
  
  ## System information
  
  GraalVM version: GraalVM CE 25.1.0-dev+9.1
  
  Operating system: Linux
  
  CPU architecture: AMD64 (x86-64)
