I want to maintain public behavior with TCCL, possibly setting it to `SimpleInstanceManagerTest.class.getClassLoader()` and restoring it later. I wonder if I need a shorter timeout and whether to use `ClassLoader` in the test, like `ClassLoader.getSystem()`. It seems feasible for loading known classes.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Evaluating class implementation**\\n\\nI’m considering whether I need annotations for InstanceManager methods from the interface and if exceptions should be added in the method throws. The reporter seems mandatory, and the existing Connector test covers everything, so no edits are needed there. \\n\\nI have to create a file within the tomcat package, using AssertJ for assertions. However, the current build has AssertJ. There’s a potential issue with accessing class constructors dynamically, especially if they’re non-public. I’m thinking about how to handle class loading with a custom TCCL and defining the ClassLoader. Let’s get writing!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_0ODXweOMRGeIJIRYcxX6l68S|fc_07bb0482083109d7016a352c6244408196ad732dde84d99dc5", "name": "write", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/org.apache.tomcat.embed/tomcat-embed-core/11.0.18/src/test/java/tomcat/SimpleInstanceManagerTest.java", "content": "/*\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\n *\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\n */\npackage tomcat;\n\nimport org.apache.tomcat.SimpleInstanceManager;\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\n\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat;\n\npublic class SimpleInstanceManagerTest {\n\n    @Test\n    void createsInstanceFromClass() throws Exception {\n        SimpleInstanceManager instanceManager = new SimpleInstanceManager();\n\n        Object instance = instanceManager.newInstance(SimpleInstanceManager.class);\n\n        assertThat(instance).isInstanceOf(SimpleInstanceManager.class);\n        assertThat(instance).isNotSameAs(instanceManager);\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    void createsInstanceFromContextClassLoader() throws Exception {\n        SimpleInstanceManager instanceManager = new SimpleInstanceManager();\n        Thread currentThread = Thread.currentThread();\n        ClassLoader originalClassLoader = currentThread.getContextClassLoader();\n        ClassLoader testClassLoader = SimpleInstanceManagerTest.class.getClassLoader();\n        currentThread.setContextClassLoader(testClassLoader);\n\n        try {\n            Object instance = instanceManager.newInstance(SimpleInstanceManager.class.getName());\n\n            assertThat(instance).isInstanceOf(SimpleInstanceManager.class);\n        } finally {\n            currentThread.setContextClassLoader(originalClassLoader);\n        }\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    void createsInstanceFromProvidedClassLoader() throws Exception {\n        SimpleInstanceManager instanceManager = new SimpleInstanceManager();\n        ClassLoader classLoader = SimpleInstanceManagerTest.class.getClassLoader();\n\n        Object instance = instanceManager.newInstance(SimpleInstanceManager.class.getName(), classLoader);\n\n        assertThat(instance).isInstanceOf(SimpleInstanceManager.class);\n    }\n}\n"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 6681, "output": 1197, "cacheRead": 11264, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 19142, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1781869644794, "responseId": "resp_07bb0482083109d7016a352c4d8630819695197b0dd01c38fb"}}
